Parse PST/OST Files with pffexport & libpff
Objectives
By completing this lab, you will:

Install and configure libpff tools for email forensics
Extract data from PST/OST files using pffexport
Analyze email artifacts and metadata
Understand the structure of Outlook data files
Perform forensic analysis on email communications
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command-line knowledge
Understanding of file systems and directory navigation
Familiarity with email concepts (headers, attachments, folders)
No prior forensics experience required
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides Linux-based cloud machines for this lab. Simply click Start Lab to access your dedicated environment. The provided Linux machine is bare metal with no pre-installed tools, so you will install all required software during the lab exercises.

Task 1: Install libpff and Required Tools
Step 1.1: Update System and Install Dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y build-essential autotools-dev automake libtool pkg-config git wget
Step 1.2: Install libpff from Source
cd /tmp
wget https://github.com/libyal/libpff/releases/download/20210424/libpff-alpha-20210424.tar.gz
tar -xzf libpff-alpha-20210424.tar.gz
cd libpff-20210424
Step 1.3: Compile and Install libpff
./configure --enable-python3
make
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig
Step 1.4: Verify Installation
pffexport -V
pffinfo -V
Expected output should show version information for both tools.

